03:55.790 --> 04:03.102
On page 396, it's worthwhile reading the 
conclusions

03:55.790 --> 04:03.102
as stated as follows. It seems that throughout the 
ages, each new weapon has been heralded as ringing

04:03.706 --> 04:08.973
the death knell of navies. Undoubtedly, this 
vicious cycle commenced with the introduction of

04:09.994 --> 04:19.067
cannons on galleys, which immediately outmoded 
the ore-propelled ram and thereby ended the reign

04:09.994 --> 04:19.067
of Sea Power. Whitehead's automotive torpedo 
assuredly placed the naval vessel in the

04:19.928 --> 04:25.095
proverbial mothballs. Sea Power then came to its 
end when Mr. Holland perfected the submarine, and

04:26.036 --> 04:31.924
again with the advent of the airplanes. but now it 
appears sea power which somehow not only managed

04:32.528 --> 04:41.412
to survive these other indefensible weapons but 
also managed to increase its influence is doomed

04:32.528 --> 04:41.412
once more. This time it is the atomic bomb that 
sends the navies to their inglorious grave. The

04:47.716 --> 05:03.158
student of history confesses that each new 
development, improvement, or invention has not

04:47.716 --> 05:03.158
diminished the naval vessel, but rather has 
expanded its importance, if not by utilization of

04:47.716 --> 05:03.158
that new invention to its own advantage, then by 
the development of defensive equipment or

04:47.716 --> 05:03.158
weapons which increased its power. Let us say, in 
general conclusion, that Operation Crossroads

05:07.038 --> 05:28.292
indicated that the destructive effect of the 
atomic bomb is 20,000 times greater than any other

05:07.038 --> 05:28.292
missile yet developed, which makes selectivity 
of targets impossible since non-military items

05:07.038 --> 05:28.292
will be destroyed just as surely as are the 
military objectives, that it can sink the largest

05:07.038 --> 05:28.292
ship afloat, and that the atomic bomb is a fact. 
This conclusion, however, has merely pointed the

05:30.494 --> 05:35.101
way for naval architects and strategists and 
tacticians. As the advent of air power only aided

05:35.863 --> 05:45.418
in making sea power stronger, so may this new 
weapon of warfare merely make naval force more

05:35.863 --> 05:45.418
effective. In page 396.

